1. load-balancing

DNS

A DNS server is a computer server that contains a database of public IP addresses and their associated hostnames, and in most cases serves to resolve, or translate, those names to IP addresses as requested.

Nginx

rount your url to different ip addresses

in order to solve web server scalability


2. catch


CDN content delivery network

A content delivery network or content distribution network (CDN) is a geographically distributed network of proxy servers and their data centers.

catch your content such as HTML, css and Javascript

in order to solve image server scalability


3. DB

Database Master-Slave Replication

Master-slave replication enables data from one database server (the master) to be replicated to one or more other database servers (the slaves).

in order to solve database read scalability

